column5: Hey all, here is a quick video of a Tiger Muskie caught while fishing smallies on lighter line.  Sinclair mentioned it is a thread he posted a week or so ago.  Going through some footage I made this small video of the fight and thought I would share. (still figuring out the editing side of things, )  <iframe width="420" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/_KVTi8xeBMg" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>  Good Fishing, Phil
Beauty gotta love them colors thanks for sharing
Wow that is one beautiful fish man.  Never caught one but its something I wish for when I am in waters that have them, right Jigger!!!
That release shot is awesome! What a pretty fish. Problem is Bucktail, you need to use more Senkos!
Cool...  I'm gunna try to get one in NY state this year...  They stock em...
